The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, June 15: President Pratibha Patil has ordered that Congress leader P.C. Thomas be barred from contesting the polls from May 19. The ban will stay for three years. He was disqualified from the Lok Sabha by Kerala High Court for seeking votes on religious grounds.           
	His disqualification was later upheld by the Supreme Court. The President had sought an opinion from the Election Commission, which had recommended that he must not be allowed to contest any election for three years. He was elected from Keralas Muvattupuzha constituency.                   
	 Ludhiana (PTI): A MiG 21 fighter aircraft of the Indian Air Force crashed near Halwara air base in Punjab around 11.15 am on Tuesday. The pilot managed to bail out safely. With this crash, the IAF has lost three fighter jets this year.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Two tyres of an Air India plane with 106 people on board were found deflated on landing at the Indira Gandhi International Airport, causing an alarm. However, the civil aviation ministry claimed there was no breach of safety in the incident involving the Mumbai- Bhopal-Indore-Delhi flight (IC-133).                  
	London (PTI): An Indian citizen who was living illegally in Britain after his asylum application was rejected has been arrested along with thr- ee Sri Lankans in the east England town of Norwich. Immigration officers arrested the four after a raid on a shop.                   
	 Kuala Lumpur (PTI): An ethnic Indian woman charged in a cheating case has been barred by a Malaysian court from going abroad and has been asked to surrender her passport. Chitrakala was charged with three counts of cheating.                  
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A two-year-old boy was kidnapped while he was sleeping outside his house in Vijay Nagar here, police said. Divyanshs mother had gone inside for some work, according to the police complaint.                                                                                                                                              
